Name: Belle London
Description: Belle London ran sprawling empire of prostitution in the back alleys of notorious two-bit street.

Name: Berthana
Description: Bertha Eccles and Anna Dee lent their names and their efforts to create a space for the youth to gather and socialize. Since it's dedication, the building has housed skating rinks, restaurants, and more.

Name: Episcopal Church
Description: This is one of the oldest churches in Ogden.

Name: Historic Union Station
Description: The rebuild union station was dedicated in the 1920s.

Name: Sarah Anderson
Description: Sarah Anderson's home was in the heart of the junction. She sued a county clerk for the right to vote.

Name: Woolworths
Description: Woolworth's offered women independence and freedom, but it came with a strict social code.
